quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,71,"The day when we will call all men by their high priest; and he whose book is given in his right hand - these shall read their book, nor shall they be wronged a straw"
  17,72,"But he who in this life is blind shall be blind in the next too, and err farther from the way"
  17,73,"They had well-nigh beguiled thee from what we inspired thee with, that thou shouldst forge against us something else, and then they would have taken thee for a friend"
  17,74,"and had it not been that we established thee, thou wouldst have well-nigh leant towards them a little"
  17,75,"then would we have made thee taste of torment both of life and death, then thou wouldst not have found against us any helper"
  17,76,"And they well-nigh enticed thee away from the land, to turn thee out therefrom; but then - they should not have tarried after thee except a little"
  17,77,"[This is] the course of those of our prophets whom we have sent before thee; and thou shalt find no change in our course"